0, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs William Hulcott was born about 1494, in Berkshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with William Hulcott."},"et":{"Abt 1494–":"umbes 1494–Surnud","1490–Male":"1490–Surnud","1520–1559":"1520–1559","1494–Female":"1494–Surnud","Abt 1494":"umbes 1494","1520":"1520","1494":"1494","about 1520":"umbes 1520","1490":"1490","1559":"1559","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, England","Barcot, Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1494–":"noin 1494–Kuollut","1490–Male":"1490–Kuollut","1520–1559":"1520–1559","1494–Female":"1494–Kuollut","Abt 1494":"noin 1494","1520":"1520","1494":"1494","about 1520":"noin 1520","1490":"1490","1559":"1559","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, England","Barcot, Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1494–":"environ 1494–Décédée","1490–Male":"1490–Décédé","1520–1559":"1520–1559","1494–Female":"1494–Décédée","Abt 1494":"environ 1494","1520":"1520","1494":"1494","about 1520":"environ 1520","1490":"1490","1559":"1559","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, Angleterre","Barcot, Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs William Hulcott est née environ 1494, à Berkshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec William Hulcott."},"de":{"Abt 1494–":"um 1494–Ver